workflow.name: OCR document processing from LINE/Gmail using GPT-4o to Google Workspace
workflow.description:
**Who this is for**

Users who frequently receive images or documents via LINE or email

Teams needing automatic OCR + AI summarization

Anyone who wants hands-free document processing and structured storage

**How it works**

Triggers: LINE Webhook and Gmail IMAP Trigger capture incoming messages or emails.

Source Tagging: Inputs are tagged as LINE or EMAIL for later branching.

File Handling: Files are uploaded to Google Drive and converted for analysis.

OCR: An AI vision model extracts all readable text from the document image.

AI Summarization: A text model produces a concise summary.

Logging: The summary is appended to Google Sheets for record-keeping.

Email Drafting: A Gmail Draft is generated containing the OCR text and summary.

**How to set up**

Connect your LINE, Gmail, OpenAI, and Google Drive/Sheets credentials.

Update folder IDs, sheet names, and authentication fields as needed.

Optional: customize summarization instructions.

**Customization ideas**

Add translation or classification steps

Modify output format for Slack/Notion

Store files in date-based Drive folders

workflow.name: Document OCR and Intelligent Summarization System

parameters.text: Transcribe all content written in this image exactly, preserving all line breaks.

parameters.content:
## Document OCR and Intelligent Summarization System

This workflow captures images or PDFs from LINE and Gmail, runs OCR and AI summarization, and stores the results so you never lose important information.

### Who it's for
- People who receive many documents as photos or email attachments  
- Anyone who wants an automatic archive of full text + short summaries in Google Sheets and Gmail

### How it works
1. Triggers on new LINE messages or Gmail inbox emails.  
2. Saves the received file to a Google Drive folder.  
3. Uses an OpenAI Vision model to extract all text from the image/PDF.  
4. Sends the text to an LLM to create a concise summary.  
5. Logs the summary in Google Sheets and prepares a Gmail draft with the OCR text and summary.

### Setup notes
- Add credentials for LINE, Gmail, Google Drive, Google Sheets, and OpenAI in your n8n instance.  
- Replace the placeholder IDs and tokens in the ‚ÄúWorkflow Configuration‚Äù node with your own values before enabling the workflow.

## Triggers & configuration

- **LINE Webhook** and **Gmail IMAP Trigger** start the workflow when a new message or email arrives.
- **Workflow Configuration** stores shared settings like Drive folder IDs and tokens.
- The **If** node makes sure we only call the LINE content API when the incoming message is an image.

Use this section to connect your own LINE bot and Gmail account before moving on to the rest of the flow.

## Source tagging & merge

- **Tag Source ‚Äì LINE / EMAIL** label each item with `source = "LINE"` or `"EMAIL"` and attach the Drive folder ID.
- **Code in JavaScript** normalizes Gmail attachments so LINE and email files share the same binary format.
- **Merge Triggers** combines both branches into a single stream so downstream nodes can treat them the same.

## File upload & OCR

- **Upload to Google Drive** saves the incoming image/PDF and outputs its file ID.
- **HTTP Request** / **HTTP Request2** download binary content from LINE and Google Drive.
- **Convert to Base64** and the vision node **Analyze image** turn the file into raw text.
- **Wait** adds a small delay to avoid rate limits and keep external APIs stable.

## Summaries & outputs

- **Message a model** turns the OCR text into a concise, human-readable summary.
- **Append row in sheet** logs each summary (and any metadata you choose) in Google Sheets.
- **Create Gmail Draft** builds a ready-to-review email that contains the OCR text, the summary, and a link to the original file.

This section is where you review or share the processed document results.

data.details:
The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.
